{{DISPLAYTITLE:<span style="text-align:center; font-size:40px; font-family:'Garamond', serif; color:#d4af37; text-shadow: 1px 1px 3px #000;">Level 5.2: "The Gilded Atrium"</span>}}

<div class="atrium-container">

{{Class 4}}

== <span class="wiki-heading">Description</span> ==
{{Blurimage|file=Mainatrium.jpg|caption=The primary area.|width=320px|font-size=10px}}{{Blurimage|file=Elevators.jpg|caption=Elevators.|width=320px|font-size=10px}}
Level 5.2, "The Gilded Atrium" is an expansive, almost boundless space that presents itself as a once-opulent Art Deco hotel from the early 20th century. The central feature is a towering, multi-tiered atrium with a glass ceiling, beneath which a perpetually overcast, gray sky can be observed. On the walls, ornately designed golden elevators stand, though most are no longer functional and show signs of decay. Dominating the scene is a grand, split staircase, its once luxurious carpet now tattered and stained.

A soft, persistent hum of a distant, somber piano melody subtly fills the space. Such melody remains constant throughout the level, regardless of one's position. The air hangs heavy with the scent of dust, dried flowers, and a faint metallic hint. The lighting remains consistently subdued, cast by tarnished brass wall sconces<ref>A sconce is a wall-mounted light fixture, often decorative, that holds a candle, lamp, or electric light.</ref> that flicker sporadically.

The central atrium consists of multiple hallways that branch out across its many floors. These corridors are lined with guest room doors, most of which remain securely locked. Occasionally, some doors can be opened to reveal rooms in various states - some appear untouched, as if ready to welcome a guest, while others are thoroughly ransacked, with furniture overturned and personal belongings scattered. A recurring detail in many rooms is a solitary, wilted flower placed in a crystal vase.

== <span class="wiki-heading">Entities</span> ==
The Gilded Atrium is home to several entities, the most prominent being <span class="entity-name">"The Bellhops."</span> These are tall, gaunt humanoid figures dressed in tattered, old-fashioned bellhop uniforms. Their faces are obscured by deep shadows, and they move with a silent, unnerving grace. They are generally non-aggressive unless a wanderer attempts to damage the level or force open a locked door. When provoked, they will pursue the individual relentlessly, their silence replaced by a chorus of discordant brass instrument sounds.

Another entity is <span class="entity-name">"The Maids,"</span> spectral figures that can be glimpsed fleetingly in the periphery, dusting furniture or arranging objects. They are intangible and will vanish if directly observed. It is believed their presence is a residual haunting, and they pose no direct threat.

More dangerous are the <span class="entity-name">"Reflections."</span> The numerous mirrors throughout the Atrium do not always show a true reflection. Occasionally, a wanderer's reflection will move independently, its expression twisting into a malevolent grin. Prolonged eye contact with a "Reflection" can lead to severe psychological distress, including paranoia and hallucinations. In rare instances, a "Reflection" may attempt to pull a wanderer into the mirror.

== <span class="wiki-heading">Colonies and Outposts</span> ==
Due to the high entity count and scarcity of resources, large-scale colonization of Level 5.2 has been deemed impossible. However, two small, highly adapted groups are known to exist.

=== <span class="sub-heading">The Archivists of the Atrium:</span> ===
* A small, reclusive group of approximately 10-15 individuals.
* They occupy a series of interconnected suites on the 7th floor, which they have heavily barricaded. The entrance is disguised as a collapsed section of the hallway.
* Their primary objective is to document the history of The Gilded Atrium, collecting journals, notes, and artifacts left by previous wanderers. They believe that by understanding the level's past, they can find a stable exit.
* The Archivists are experts at avoiding the Bellhops and have developed methods for safely observing "Reflections" without succumbing to their psychological effects, often using periscopes or angled mirrors.
* They are cautious but generally open to trade with solitary wanderers. They value information, batteries, and untainted food sources above all else, often trading their own documented findings or the rare vial of Almond Water found in the level.

=== <span class="sub-heading">The Gilded Ghosts:</span> ===
* A mysterious and highly elusive group of unknown size. It is unclear if they are a formal colony or a loose collection of long-term survivors who have been psychologically altered by the level.
* They do not have a known base but are rumored to inhabit the maintenance corridors and non-functional elevator shafts.
* Their behavior is erratic and unpredictable. Some wanderers have reported receiving cryptic guidance from them, while others have been led into traps or directly into the path of provoked Bellhops.
* The Gilded Ghosts seem to have a strange, almost symbiotic relationship with the level. They have been observed mimicking the silent movements of the Bellhops and are adept at using the mirrored surfaces to appear and disappear, making it difficult to determine if they are human or a new form of entity entirely. Direct contact is not advised.

== <span class="wiki-heading">Entrances and Exits</span> ==
=== <span class="sub-heading">Entrances:</span> ===
* Finding and entering an old, ornate, out-of-place elevator in certain urban levels and pressing the "Lobby" button can lead here.
* Random noclippage in [[Level 5]] can lead here.

=== <span class="sub-heading">Exits:</span> ===
* Locating a functional elevator and taking it to the "Roof Garden" will reportedly lead to [[Level 94]].
* Finding a pristine, fully-furnished guest room and sleeping in the bed may transport the wanderer to [[Level 974]].
* Certain unlocked maintenance doors in the hallways, often marked with the symbol of The Archivists, may lead to the boiler room of [[Level 5]].
